6:
Stella! Are you all right? Please, say 
something! Anything!
10: Stella! Come back to us! Stella!
36:
Don't worry. This is my place. You're 
safe now.
I'm gonna go call the others.
48:
I thought it might help you sleep 
better. But it was so quiet, I'm surprised 
you picked up on it.
52: You truly... have a beautiful voice.
70:
Can't believe you just blacked out on 
us. We were scared out of our minds... 
How you feeling now?
74: Fine. We need to set out.
78:
You are NOT fine. I have sensors, and 
they're telling me you're overheated.
82:
Let us stay here a while longer. The 
search for the World Flipper can 
continue after you've recovered.
94:
There's a droid. Just down the street. 
He knows a lot about humans... More 
than I do, at least. Maybe he could 
help…
96:
The thing is, I don't have any tools that 
can, um, be used for human 
maintenance.
107:
So... he's as slippery as an oil puddle, 
and just as annoying to deal with... But 
he pulls through when you need him.
119:
Well, hello! Welcome to mi casa. 
I've been waiting for you.
I'm Rec Register. But I insist you call me 
Regis, as a sign of our friendship.
122:
You know, I've always wanted to meet 
a human, ever since I first read about 
them in some moldy corner of the 
internet. And now here you are! I'd cry 
if I had tear ducts. Or eyes.
126:
Oh, where are my manners?! Please sit, 
sit. No need to stand like Sunday 
school children in the presence of the 
headmaster. Kick your feet up! 
Make yourself at home!
131: He strokes my fur the wrong way...
134:
Er... Regis. How did you know we were 
coming?
137:
A charming little canary called and 
told me to set up a grand reception in 
five minutes. And, by the by, I also 
know what this party is all about.
142:
First off, there's no food here. None of 
the solid stuff you fellows eat, at any 
rate. And by "here," I don't just mean at 
my house. I mean on this planet.
146: Oh. Thaaat's... a really big problem...
150:
We derive our energy from food. 
Without it, we'll cease to function.
157:
Yes. And second off, you're a band of 
wanted criminals.
159:
I can't risk our golden canary being 
seen with you. Understand?
164: Loud and clear. Let's go, guys.
167:
Wait. Dia darling, were you not 
listening to a word I just said?
171:
So what? Let the press have a field 
day! "Diva Media, rendezvousing with 
humans in the night?!"
175:
Don't be funny. You're performing for 
the Administrator tomorrow!
179:
I don't CARE about the Administrator, 
okay? Half the time, I can't tell if she's 
awake, or just sleep-talking!
185:
The creator of all droids. She always 
said music brings us closer to 
humans.
186:
And Dia here just happens to be her 
golden canary. All her concerts are like 
rituals, you see. Songs sung in 
celebration of the Administrator.
190:
Yeah. It'd sure suck if I went missing, 
huh?
192: Come on, Regis. I'm not leaving them!
197:
...Oh, okay, okay! I just need to get 
these folks home, right?
206: Heh. Not bad, miss metal mask.
208:
Well, we won't do any good hanging 
around here. I'm sorry, Stella dear, but 
we're going to have to move.
209:
And what's more, we're going to have 
to do it out of sight of any droids.
We'll go by paths infested with bugs. 
Hope you have your pesticide ready.
